post_text:
No matter what phase New Orleans chooses for school opening, we are ready!

In the event that we return to campus, we have prepared our building, gathered supplies, and trained staff to make sure in-person school is safe with quality learning. If we will be distance learning, staff will be ready and trained on innovative and high-quality learning options!

While this situation feels impossible, we are ready to support our scholars and families to make sure learning continues as best it can.

Is your child missing camp this summer? Send them to Camp Kinda!

Camp Kinda is a free, virtual summer camp experience designed to keep kids engaged, asking questions, and having fun even while they‚Äôre stuck at home ‚õ∫ Each weekday from June 1 to September 1, participating families will get 3-4 hours‚Äô worth of daily activities, all connected to a weekly theme and curated by experts with a passion for their topic.

On any given day, kids may be exploring the art of graphic novels, unlocking the mysteries of history, or jumping into the world‚Äôs craziest sports üîç üèÄ ü§î

With a mix of online and offline activities, Camp Kinda is flexible enough to let you pick and choose what you put in front of your kids (and when), but kid-driven enough to let you step away. To learn more and sign up for free, visit CampKinda.org & use the registration code CCS20.

post_text:
Congratulations to Celsey, our first Distance Learning Scholar of the Week! She has done excellent #HabansFromHome work: Celsey completed all of her assignments, and was the FIRST sixth-grade student to submit her math assignment in Google Classroom!

She also FaceTimed with her teacher to ensure she was connected and understood all the directions to her science assignments, called her friends to ensure they were doing assignments, share the computer with her brother when he needed it. She has been in constant contact with her teachers whenever there is a tech issue, and she is eager for feedback‚Äîshe even called her ELA teacher to ask if she had any feedback for her on Friday!

Celsey will have PIZZA sent to her house (with parent permission) as a reward for all her hard work!

To nominate your student submit a photo using the hashtag #habansfromhome and tag us! Explain why they deserve to be our Distance Learning Scholar of the Week!
